ropshire, England":"Bridgnorth, Shropshire, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1376–":"omkring 1376–Afdød","1371–1456":"1371–1456","1392–1456":"1392–1456","1394–1442":"1394–1442","1376–Female":"1376–Afdød","1456":"1456","1376":"1376","1442":"1442","about 1376":"omkring 1376","1394":"1394","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom","Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England":"Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England"},"nl":{"about 1376–":"circa 1376–Overleden","1371–1456":"1371–1456","1392–1456":"1392–1456","1394–1442":"1394–1442","1376–Female":"1376–Overleden","1456":"1456","1376":"1376","1442":"1442","about 1376":"circa 1376","1394":"1394","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England":"Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England"},"en":{"about 1376–":"about 1376–Deceased","1371–1456":"1371–1456","1392–1456":"1392–1456","1394–1442":"1394–1442","1376–Female":"1376–Deceased","1456":"1456","1376":"1376","1442":"1442","about 1376":"about 1376","1394":"1394","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom","Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England":"Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Sutherland","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish (Caithness): habitational name from the Scottish county of Sutherland, named with Old Norse <i>súthr</i> ‘south, southern’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’ because the territory lay south of Scandinavia and the Norse colonies in the Orkney and Shetland Islands.","History: This is the name of a Highland Scottish clan associated with the county of Sutherland."],"variants":[{"name":"Southerland","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Sutherland  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Sutherland was born about 1376, in Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Walter de Grene of Bridgnorth. She died in Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1376–":"umbes 1376–Surnud","1371–1456":"1371–1456","1392–1456":"1392–1456","1394–1442":"1394–1442","1376–Female":"1376–Surnud","1456":"1456","1376":"1376","1442":"1442","about 1376":"umbes 1376","1394":"1394","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom","Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England":"Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1376–":"noin 1376–Kuollut","1371–1456":"1371–1456","1392–1456":"1392–1456","1394–1442":"1394–1442","1376–Female":"1376–Kuollut","1456":"1456","1376":"1376","1442":"1442","about 1376":"noin 1376","1394":"1394","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England":"Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1376–":"environ 1376–Décédée","1371–1456":"1371–1456","1392–1456":"1392–1456","1394–1442":"1394–1442","1376–Female":"1376–Décédée","1456":"1456","1376":"1376","1442":"1442","about 1376":"environ 1376","1394":"1394","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England":"Bridgnorth, Shropshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Margaret Sutherland est née environ 1376, à Bridgnorth, Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Walter de Grene of Bridgnorth. Elle est décédée à Gwynedd, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"about 1376–":"um 1376–Verstorben","1371–1456":"1371–1456","1392–1456":"1392–1456","1394–1442":"1394–1442","1376–Female":"1376–Verstorben","1456":"1456","1376":"1376","1442":"1442","about 1376":"um 1376","1394":"1394","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","Gwynedd, Wales":"Gwynedd, Wales, United Kingdom","Bridgnorth, S